{
  "stem": "812.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Three of their six children had polio in Bergen-Belsen and survived.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were in quarantine but miraculously survived.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My dear friend Susie was one of them, who is now in Israel.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] She was even paralyzed and here without medication, without even anything physically to fall back on-- no strength, no food, no nothing.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They survived.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That is a true miracle.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That's when we know, yes, there is a man upstairs.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We can be angry with Him, though, and can't help but-- but doing that once in a while.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I had major conversations with the man upstairs.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I-- somehow I always come away feeling all right.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] It was decided that my brother and I would go to Bussum and live in this Youth Aliyah home.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My mother decided to stay in Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "She [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] eventually moved in-- or my-- actually, it was my aunt, my father's sister, who was in hiding in Holland, came forth, and we found one another.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And this Aunt Rosie, who also had most of our belongings in hiding with her-- and that's why we were able to save so many documents and personal items was through her-- this Aunt Rosie moved in with my mother in Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "My mother decided to study masseuse, manicure, and pedicure.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "This had to be done in Dutch.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "She never knew Dutch, and she had to learn all of these tissues and muscles and-- and whatnot in Dutch.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "She's a very, very industrious lady, my mother, and of course did very well and got her diploma or degree.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And with it, she eventually was able to get a bicycle.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
